## ⚡ Why this can fail (Common Mistakes)

```jsx
loader: async ({ params }) => {
  const res = await fetch("./products.json");  // ❌ relative path fails
  const data = await res.json();
  return data.find(p => p.id === params.productId);
}
```

This usually works in development but **fails after build** because `./products.json` isn’t found anymore.

✅ Fix → use `/products.json` (root, public folder), not `./`.

