## Fetching dynamic data

## **Option 1: Pass full product data via state**

In `ProductDemoHome`:

```jsx
<button 
  onClick={() => navigate(`productsDemo/${item.id}`, { state: item })}
>
  {item.title}
</button>
```

In `ProductDemo`:

```jsx
import { useLocation } from "react-router";

const ProductDemo = () => {
  const { state: product } = useLocation();

  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Product Details Page</h2>
      {product ? (
        <div>
          <p><strong>Title:</strong> {product.title}</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong> {product.description}</p>
        </div>
      ) : (
        <p>Product not found!</p>
      )}
    </div>
  );
};
```

✅ **Pros:** Simple for small apps, no extra loader needed.

---

## **Option 2: Use a loader for the detail page**

In your route:

```js
{
  path: 'productsDemo/:productDemoID',
  Component: ProductDemo,
  loader: async ({ params }) => {
    const res = await fetch('/product.json');
    const data = await res.json();
    return data.find(p => p.id === parseInt(params.productDemoID));
  }
}
```

In `ProductDemo`:

```jsx
import { useLoaderData } from "react-router";

const ProductDemo = () => {
  const product = useLoaderData();

  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Product Details Page</h2>
      <p><strong>Title:</strong> {product.title}</p>
      <p><strong>Description:</strong> {product.description}</p>
    </div>
  );
};
```

✅ **Pros:** Cleaner, works with refresh/reload because data is fetched per route.

💡 **Summary:**

* Use **state via `navigate`** for fast navigation without refetch.
* Use **loader** on detail route if you want proper URL-based fetching and refresh support.

